[1] Syria, 7 new cases cVDPV - WHO/UNICEF Sit Rep 16 4 Oct 2017
Date: Tue 3 Oct 2017
Source: Relief Web [edited]
https://reliefweb.int/report/syrian-arab-republic/syria-cvdpv2-outbreak-situation-report-16-3-october-2017


Key highlights
- Seven (7) new cases of cVDPV2 have been confirmed this week [week of Sun 1 Oct 2017] - 5 cases from Mayadeen and one from Boukamal districts, Deir Ez-Zor governorate, and one case from Thawra district (newly infected), Raqqa governorate. Isolates from some cases had been laboratory pending for some time. The most recent case, a child from Boukamal with no history of polio vaccination, had onset of paralysis on [5 Aug 2017].
- The total number of cVDPV2 cases is 47.
- Poliovirus has been isolated from stool samples collected from a healthy child in Damascus, as part of screening in place for IPDs from Deir Ez-Zor and Raqqa. The child, from Boukamal, Deir Ez-Zor, had samples collected on [19 Aug 2017], the day of arrival. WHO and MoH will continue to take samples from healthy children in areas of Damascus with high numbers of IDPs, to ensure there is no wider circulation.
- Preparation for the 2nd immunization round for Raqqa is ongoing. Newly accessible villages in Thawra district have been included in campaign plans.
- A series of meetings between partners to review outbreak response activities to date and to identify priorities for the next 2 months took place in Beirut [29-30 Sep 2017].

Summary
New cVDPV2 cases this week: 7
Total number of cVDPV2 cases: 47

Infected governorates and districts
Governorate: District - Number of cVDPV2 cases to date
