[The important take away messages in the above reports are:
- The outbreak of cVDPV in Syria is continuing, with the total number of cVDPV cases reported from Syria now at 47. The outbreak primarily involves Deir-al-Zour governorate, but there is now a 2nd case in Raqqah governorate in a 2nd district. Given the time interval from dates of onset to dates of confirmation (most likely due to logistic challenges to collect and transport laboratory specimens), it appears as though there may well be more cases reported in the coming days and weeks (I hope I am wrong with this prediction).
- The isolation of the virus in asymptomatic individuals serves to highlight the virus is still circulating in the country, and the isolation of the virus in a refugee entering the capital city of Damascus points out the risks of continued spread in the country..
- While there were no newly confirmed paralytic cases in Afghanistan and Pakistan reported in the past week [week of Sun 24 Sep 2017], the isolation of the WPV in environmental samples serves to highlight that the virus is still circulating in Pakistan.

A map showing the global distribution of all WPV1 associated cases and cVDPV associated cases can be found at:http://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now/. A map showing the locations of the cases of cVDPV2 in Syria can be found at the source url in section [1] above.

